oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Practical application of techniques for performing C-sections in beef cows
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Lewis, Keelan
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: dystocia
calving
C-section
cesarean
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: As a newly graduated veterinarian, the idea of a calf delivery via cesarean section is daunting. As a young veterinarian I would avoid c-sections so readily I would be exhausted by the time the procedure was the last remaining option. Mentorship and functional tricks can help avoid this misguided fear in new veterinarians.
